  "prompt": "How do we forget any Wi-Fi in Windows 10?",
  "response": "To forget a Wi-Fi network in Windows 10, follow these steps:\n\n1. Open Settings\n- Click the Start menu\n- Click the \"Settings\" gear icon\n- Or press Windows Key + I\n\n2. Click on \"Network & Internet\"\n\n3. Select \"Wi-Fi\" from the left sidebar\n\n4. Click on \"Manage known networks\"\n\n5. Find the network you want to forget\n\n6. Click on the network\n\n7. Click \"Forget\"\n\nAlternatively, you can also do this through Control Panel:\n\n1. Open Control Panel\n2. Go to \"Network and Internet\"\n3. Click \"Network and Sharing Center\"\n4. Click \"Change adapter settings\"\n5. Right-click on the wireless network connection\n6. Select \"Status\"\n7. Click \"Wireless Properties\"\n8. Go to the \"Security\" tab\n9. Uncheck \"Connect automatically\"\n10. Click \"OK\"\n\nAnother quick method:\n- Open the Wi-Fi network list\n- Right-click on the saved network\n- Select \"Forget\"\n\nAfter forgetting a network, you'll need to reconnect and re-enter the password if you want to use it again.",
